The regulation requires a disclosure for institutions offering time accounts that compound interest and permit
a consumer to withdraw accrued interest during the account term. The disclosure states that the APY assumes interest
remains on deposit until maturity and that a withdrawal of interest will reduce earnings. The Board request comments
